30 uint32 GetTargetFlagMask(SpellTargetObjectTypes objType)
31 {
32  switch (objType)
33  {
34  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
35  return TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION;
36  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
37  return TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT;
38  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE_ALLY:
39  return TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ALLY;
40  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE_ENEMY:
41  return TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ENEMY;
42  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE:
43  return TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ALLY | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ENEMY;
44  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT:
45  return TARGET_FLAG_UNIT;
46  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
47  return TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT;
48  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ_ITEM:
49  return TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM;
50  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_ITEM:
51  return TARGET_FLAG_ITEM;
52  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_SRC:
53  return TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION;
54  default:
55  return TARGET_FLAG_NONE;
56  }
57 }

94 float SpellImplicitTargetInfo::CalcDirectionAngle() const
95 {
96  switch (GetDirectionType())
97  {
98  case TARGET_DIR_FRONT:
99  return 0.0f;
100  case TARGET_DIR_BACK:
101  return static_cast<float>(M_PI);
102  case TARGET_DIR_RIGHT:
103  return static_cast<float>(-M_PI / 2);
104  case TARGET_DIR_LEFT:
105  return static_cast<float>(M_PI / 2);
106  case TARGET_DIR_FRONT_RIGHT:
107  return static_cast<float>(-M_PI / 4);
108  case TARGET_DIR_BACK_RIGHT:
109  return static_cast<float>(-3 * M_PI / 4);
110  case TARGET_DIR_BACK_LEFT:
111  return static_cast<float>(3 * M_PI / 4);
112  case TARGET_DIR_FRONT_LEFT:
113  return static_cast<float>(M_PI / 4);
114  case TARGET_DIR_RANDOM:
115  return float(rand_norm()) * static_cast<float>(2 * M_PI);
116  default:
117  return 0.0f;
118  }
119 }

126 uint32 SpellImplicitTargetInfo::GetExplicitTargetMask(bool& srcSet, bool& dstSet) const
127 {
128  uint32 targetMask = 0;
129  if (GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_TRAJ)
130  {
131  if (!srcSet)
132  targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION;
133  if (!dstSet)
134  targetMask |= TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION;
135  }
136  else
137  {
138  switch (GetReferenceType())
139  {
140  case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_SRC:
141  if (srcSet)
142  break;
143  targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION;
144  break;
145  case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_DEST:
146  if (dstSet)
147  break;
148  targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION;
149  break;
150  case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_TARGET:
151  switch (GetObjectType())
152  {
153  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
154  targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT;
155  break;
156  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ_ITEM:
157  targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM;
158  break;
159  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
160  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT:
161  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
162  switch (GetCheckType())
163  {
164  case TARGET_CHECK_ENEMY:
165  targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY;
166  break;
167  case TARGET_CHECK_ALLY:
168  targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY;
169  break;
170  case TARGET_CHECK_PARTY:
171  targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY;
172  break;
173  case TARGET_CHECK_RAID:
174  targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID;
175  break;
176  case TARGET_CHECK_PASSENGER:
177  targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PASSENGER;
178  break;
179  case TARGET_CHECK_RAID_CLASS:
180  [[fallthrough]];
181  default:
182  targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT;
183  break;
184  }
185  break;
186  default:
187  break;
188  }
189  break;
190  default:
191  break;
192  }
193  }
194 
195  switch (GetObjectType())
196  {
197  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_SRC:
198  srcSet = true;
199  break;
200  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
201  case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
202  dstSet = true;
203  break;
204  default:
205  break;
206  }
207  return targetMask;
208 }

325 SpellEffectInfo::SpellEffectInfo(SpellEntry const* spellEntry, SpellInfo const* spellInfo, uint8 effIndex)
326 {
327  _spellInfo = spellInfo;
328  _effIndex = effIndex;
329  Effect = spellEntry->Effect[effIndex];
330  ApplyAuraName = spellEntry->EffectApplyAuraName[effIndex];
331  Amplitude = spellEntry->EffectAmplitude[effIndex];
332  DieSides = spellEntry->EffectDieSides[effIndex];
333  RealPointsPerLevel = spellEntry->EffectRealPointsPerLevel[effIndex];
334  BasePoints = spellEntry->EffectBasePoints[effIndex];
335  PointsPerComboPoint = spellEntry->EffectPointsPerComboPoint[effIndex];
336  ValueMultiplier = spellEntry->EffectValueMultiplier[effIndex];
337  DamageMultiplier = spellEntry->EffectDamageMultiplier[effIndex];
338  BonusMultiplier = spellEntry->EffectBonusMultiplier[effIndex];
339  MiscValue = spellEntry->EffectMiscValue[effIndex];
340  MiscValueB = spellEntry->EffectMiscValueB[effIndex];
341  Mechanic = Mechanics(spellEntry->EffectMechanic[effIndex]);
342  TargetA = SpellImplicitTargetInfo(spellEntry->EffectImplicitTargetA[effIndex]);
343  TargetB = SpellImplicitTargetInfo(spellEntry->EffectImplicitTargetB[effIndex]);
344  RadiusEntry = spellEntry->EffectRadiusIndex[effIndex] ? sSpellRadiusStore.LookupEntry(spellEntry->EffectRadiusIndex[effIndex]) : nullptr;
345  ChainTarget = spellEntry->EffectChainTarget[effIndex];
346  ItemType = spellEntry->EffectItemType[effIndex];
347  TriggerSpell = spellEntry->EffectTriggerSpell[effIndex];
348  SpellClassMask = spellEntry->EffectSpellClassMask[effIndex];
349  ImplicitTargetConditions = nullptr;
350 }

408 int32 SpellEffectInfo::CalcValue(Unit const* caster, int32 const* bp, Unit const* /*target*/) const
409 {
410  float basePointsPerLevel = RealPointsPerLevel;
411  int32 basePoints = bp ? *bp : BasePoints;
412  int32 randomPoints = int32(DieSides);
413 
414  // base amount modification based on spell lvl vs caster lvl
415  // xinef: added basePointsPerLevel check
416  if (caster && basePointsPerLevel != 0.0f)
417  {
418  int32 level = int32(caster->getLevel());
419  if (level > int32(_spellInfo->MaxLevel) && _spellInfo->MaxLevel > 0)
420  level = int32(_spellInfo->MaxLevel);
421  else if (level < int32(_spellInfo->BaseLevel))
422  level = int32(_spellInfo->BaseLevel);
423 
424  // xinef: if base level is greater than spell level, reduce by base level (eg. pilgrims foods)
425  level -= int32(std::max(_spellInfo->BaseLevel, _spellInfo->SpellLevel));
426  basePoints += int32(level * basePointsPerLevel);
427  }
428 
429  // roll in a range <1;EffectDieSides> as of patch 3.3.3
430  switch (randomPoints)
431  {
432  case 0:
433  break;
434  case 1:
435  basePoints += 1;
436  break; // range 1..1
437  default:
438  // range can have positive (1..rand) and negative (rand..1) values, so order its for irand
439  int32 randvalue = (randomPoints >= 1)
440  ? irand(1, randomPoints)
441  : irand(randomPoints, 1);
442 
443  basePoints += randvalue;
444  break;
445  }
446 
447  float value = float(basePoints);
448 
449  // random damage
450  if (caster)
451  {
452  // bonus amount from combo points
453  if (caster->m_movedByPlayer)
454  if (uint8 comboPoints = caster->m_movedByPlayer->ToPlayer()->GetComboPoints())
455  if (float comboDamage = PointsPerComboPoint)
456  value += comboDamage * comboPoints;
457 
458  value = caster->ApplyEffectModifiers(_spellInfo, _effIndex, value);
459 
460  // amount multiplication based on caster's level
461  if (!caster->IsControlledByPlayer() &&
462  _spellInfo->SpellLevel && _spellInfo->SpellLevel != caster->getLevel() &&
463  !basePointsPerLevel && _spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_SCALES_WITH_CREATURE_LEVEL))
464  {
465  bool canEffectScale = false;
466  switch (Effect)
467  {
468  case SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE:
469  case SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY:
470  case SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_DRAIN:
471  case SPELL_EFFECT_HEALTH_LEECH:
472  case SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL:
473  case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE:
474  case SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_BURN:
475  case SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT:
476  case SPELL_EFFECT_NORMALIZED_WEAPON_DMG:
477  case SPELL_EFFECT_FORCE_CAST_WITH_VALUE:
478  case SPELL_EFFECT_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
479  case SPELL_EFFECT_TRIGGER_MISSILE_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
480  canEffectScale = true;
481  break;
482  default:
483  break;
484  }
485 
486  switch (ApplyAuraName)
487  {
488  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
489  case SPELL_AURA_DUMMY:
490  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
491  case SPELL_AURA_DAMAGE_SHIELD:
492  case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_DAMAGE:
493  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
494  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_MANA_LEECH:
495  case SPELL_AURA_SCHOOL_ABSORB:
496  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
497  canEffectScale = true;
498  break;
499  default:
500  break;
501  }
502 
503  if (canEffectScale)
504  {
505  GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* spellScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.LookupEntry(_spellInfo->SpellLevel - 1);
506  GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* casterScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.LookupEntry(caster->getLevel() - 1);
507  if (spellScaler && casterScaler)
508  value *= casterScaler->ratio / spellScaler->ratio;
509  }
510  }
511  }
512 
513  return int32(value);
514 }

520  else

540 bool SpellEffectInfo::HasRadius() const
541 {
542  return RadiusEntry != nullptr;
543 }
544 
545 float SpellEffectInfo::CalcRadius(Unit* caster, Spell* spell) const
546 {
547  if (!HasRadius())
548  return 0.0f;
549 
550  float radius = RadiusEntry->RadiusMin;
551  if (caster)
552  {
553  radius += RadiusEntry->RadiusPerLevel * caster->getLevel();
554  radius = std::min(radius, RadiusEntry->RadiusMax);
555  if (Player* modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
556  modOwner->ApplySpellMod(_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_RADIUS, radius, spell);
557  }
558 
559  return radius;
560 }

567 uint32 SpellEffectInfo::GetMissingTargetMask(bool srcSet /*= false*/, bool dstSet /*= false*/, uint32 mask /*=0*/) const
568 {
569  uint32 effImplicitTargetMask = GetTargetFlagMask(GetUsedTargetObjectType());
570  uint32 providedTargetMask = GetTargetFlagMask(TargetA.GetObjectType()) | GetTargetFlagMask(TargetB.GetObjectType()) | mask;
571 
572  // remove all flags covered by effect target mask
573  if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK)
574  effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK);
575  if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK)
576  effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK);
577  if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM)
578  effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_ITEM);
579  if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT)
580  effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM);
581  if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_ITEM)
582  effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_ITEM | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM);
583  if (dstSet || providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
584  effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION);
585  if (srcSet || providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION)
586  effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION);
587 
588  return effImplicitTargetMask;
589 }

912  (Effects[0].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_CREATE_ITEM_2 &&
913  ((TotemCategory[0] != 0 || (Totem[0] != 0 && SpellIconID == 1)) || Effects[0].ItemType == 0)));
914 }

971 bool SpellInfo::IsAbilityLearnedWithProfession() const
972 {
973  SkillLineAbilityMapBounds bounds = sSpellMgr->GetSkillLineAbilityMapBounds(Id);
974 
975  for (SkillLineAbilityMap::const_iterator _spell_idx = bounds.first; _spell_idx != bounds.second; ++_spell_idx)
976  {
977  SkillLineAbilityEntry const* pAbility = _spell_idx->second;
978  if (!pAbility || pAbility->AcquireMethod != SKILL_LINE_ABILITY_LEARNED_ON_SKILL_VALUE)
979  continue;
980 
981  if (pAbility->MinSkillLineRank > 0)
982  return true;
983  }
984 
985  return false;
986 }
987 
988 bool SpellInfo::IsAbilityOfSkillType(uint32 skillType) const
989 {
990  SkillLineAbilityMapBounds bounds = sSpellMgr->GetSkillLineAbilityMapBounds(Id);
991 
992  for (SkillLineAbilityMap::const_iterator _spell_idx = bounds.first; _spell_idx != bounds.second; ++_spell_idx)
993  if (_spell_idx->second->SkillLine == uint32(skillType))
994  return true;
995 
996  return false;
997 }

999 bool SpellInfo::IsAffectingArea() const
1000 {
1001  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1002  if (Effects[i].IsEffect() && (Effects[i].IsTargetingArea() || Effects[i].IsEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_PERSISTENT_AREA_AURA) || Effects[i].IsAreaAuraEffect()))
1003  return true;
1004  return false;
1005 }

1007 // checks if spell targets are selected from area, doesn't include spell effects in check (like area wide auras for example)
1008 bool SpellInfo::IsTargetingArea() const

1414 SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckShapeshift(uint32 form) const
1415 {
1416  // talents that learn spells can have stance requirements that need ignore
1417  // (this requirement only for client-side stance show in talent description)
1418  if (GetTalentSpellCost(Id) > 0 &&
1419  (Effects[0].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL || Effects[1].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL || Effects[2].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL))
1420  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1421 
1422  uint32 stanceMask = (form ? 1 << (form - 1) : 0);
1423 
1424  if (stanceMask & StancesNot) // can explicitly not be casted in this stance
1425  return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_SHAPESHIFT;
1426 
1427  if (stanceMask & Stances) // can explicitly be casted in this stance
1428  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1429 
1430  bool actAsShifted = false;
1431  SpellShapeshiftEntry const* shapeInfo = nullptr;
1432  if (form > 0)
1433  {
1434  shapeInfo = sSpellShapeshiftStore.LookupEntry(form);
1435  if (!shapeInfo)
1436  {
1437  LOG_ERROR("spells", "GetErrorAtShapeshiftedCast: unknown shapeshift %u", form);
1438  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1439  }
1440  actAsShifted = !(shapeInfo->flags1 & 1); // shapeshift acts as normal form for spells
1441  }
1442 
1443  if (actAsShifted)
1444  {
1445  if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_NOT_SHAPESHIFTED)) // not while shapeshifted
1446  return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_SHAPESHIFT;
1447  else if (Stances != 0) // needs other shapeshift
1448  return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_SHAPESHIFT;
1449  }
1450  else
1451  {
1452  // needs shapeshift
1453  if (!(AttributesEx2 & SPELL_ATTR2_ALLOW_WHILE_NOT_SHAPESHIFTED) && Stances != 0)
1454  return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_SHAPESHIFT;
1455  }
1456 
1457  // Check if stance disables cast of not-stance spells
1458  // Example: cannot cast any other spells in zombie or ghoul form
1459  // TODO: Find a way to disable use of these spells clientside
1460  if (shapeInfo && shapeInfo->flags1 & 0x400)
1461  {
1462  if (!(stanceMask & Stances))
1463  return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_SHAPESHIFT;
1464  }
1465 
1466  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1467 }

1469 SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckLocation(uint32 map_id, uint32 zone_id, uint32 area_id, Player const* player /*= nullptr*/, bool strict /*= true*/) const
1470 {
1471  // normal case
1472  if (AreaGroupId > 0)
1473  {
1474  bool found = false;
1475  AreaGroupEntry const* groupEntry = sAreaGroupStore.LookupEntry(AreaGroupId);
1476  while (groupEntry)
1477  {
1478  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_GROUP_AREA_IDS; ++i)
1479  if (groupEntry->AreaId[i] == zone_id || groupEntry->AreaId[i] == area_id)
1480  found = true;
1481  if (found || !groupEntry->nextGroup)
1482  break;
1483  // Try search in next group
1484  groupEntry = sAreaGroupStore.LookupEntry(groupEntry->nextGroup);
1485  }
1486 
1487  if (!found)
1488  return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1489  }
1490 
1491  // continent limitation (virtual continent)
1492  if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_ONLY_FLYING_AREAS))
1493  {
1494  AreaTableEntry const* areaEntry = sAreaTableStore.LookupEntry(area_id);
1495  if (!areaEntry)
1496  {
1497  areaEntry = sAreaTableStore.LookupEntry(zone_id);
1498  }
1499 
1500  if (!areaEntry || !areaEntry->IsFlyable() || (strict && (areaEntry->flags & AREA_FLAG_NO_FLY_ZONE) != 0) || !player->canFlyInZone(map_id, zone_id, this))
1501  {
1502  return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1503  }
1504  }
1505 
1506  // raid instance limitation
1507  if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR6_NOT_IN_RAID_INSTANCES))
1508  {
1509  MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1510  if (!mapEntry || mapEntry->IsRaid())
1511  return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_IN_RAID_INSTANCE;
1512  }
1513 
1514  // DB base check (if non empty then must fit at least single for allow)
1515  SpellAreaMapBounds saBounds = sSpellMgr->GetSpellAreaMapBounds(Id);
1516  if (saBounds.first != saBounds.second)
1517  {
1518  for (SpellAreaMap::const_iterator itr = saBounds.first; itr != saBounds.second; ++itr)
1519  {
1520  if (itr->second.IsFitToRequirements(player, zone_id, area_id))
1521  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1522  }
1523  return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1524  }
1525 
1526  // bg spell checks
1527  switch (Id)
1528  {
1529  case 23333: // Warsong Flag
1530  case 23335: // Silverwing Flag
1531  return map_id == 489 && player && player->InBattleground() ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1532  case 34976: // Netherstorm Flag
1533  return map_id == 566 && player && player->InBattleground() ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1534  case 2584: // Waiting to Resurrect
1535  case 22011: // Spirit Heal Channel
1536  case 22012: // Spirit Heal
1537  case 24171: // Resurrection Impact Visual
1538  case 42792: // Recently Dropped Flag
1539  case 43681: // Inactive
1540  case 44535: // Spirit Heal (mana)
1541  {
1542  MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1543  if (!mapEntry)
1544  return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1545 
1546  return zone_id == 4197 || (mapEntry->IsBattleground() && player && player->InBattleground()) ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1547  }
1548  case 32724: // Gold Team (Alliance)
1549  case 32725: // Green Team (Alliance)
1550  case 35774: // Gold Team (Horde)
1551  case 35775: // Green Team (Horde)
1552  {
1553  MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1554  if (!mapEntry)
1555  return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1556 
1557  return mapEntry->IsBattleArena() && player && player->InBattleground() ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1558  }
1559  }
1560 
1561  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1562 }
1563 
1564 bool SpellInfo::IsStrongerAuraActive(Unit const* caster, Unit const* target) const
1565 {
1566  if (!target)
1567  return false;
1568 
1569  // xinef: check spell group
1570  uint32 groupId = sSpellMgr->GetSpellGroup(Id);
1571  if (!groupId)
1572  return false;
1573 
1574  SpellGroupSpecialFlags sFlag = sSpellMgr->GetSpellGroupSpecialFlags(Id);
1575  if (sFlag & SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_SKIP_STRONGER_CHECK)
1576  return false;
1577 
1578  for (uint8 i = EFFECT_0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1579  {
1580  // xinef: Skip Empty effects
1581  if (!Effects[i].IsEffect())
1582  continue;
1583 
1584  // xinef: if non-aura effect is preset - return false
1585  if (!Effects[i].IsAura())
1586  return false;
1587 
1588  // xinef: aura is periodic - return false
1589  if (Effects[i].Amplitude)
1590  return false;
1591 
1592  // xinef: exclude dummy auras
1593  if (Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_DUMMY)
1594  return false;
1595  }
1596 
1597  for (uint8 i = EFFECT_0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1598  {
1599  // xinef: skip non-aura efects
1600  if (!Effects[i].IsAura())
1601  return false;
1602 
1603  Unit::AuraEffectList const& auraList = target->GetAuraEffectsByType((AuraType)Effects[i].ApplyAuraName);
1604  for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator iter = auraList.begin(); iter != auraList.end(); ++iter)
1605  {
1606  // xinef: aura is not groupped or in different group
1607  uint32 auraGroup = (*iter)->GetAuraGroup();
1608  if (!auraGroup || auraGroup != groupId)
1609  continue;
1610 
1611  // xinef: check priority before effect mask
1612  if (sFlag >= SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_PRIORITY1)
1613  {
1614  SpellGroupSpecialFlags sFlagCurr = sSpellMgr->GetSpellGroupSpecialFlags((*iter)->GetId());
1615  if (sFlagCurr >= SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_PRIORITY1 && sFlagCurr < sFlag)
1616  return true;
1617  }
1618 
1619  // xinef: check aura effect equal auras only, some auras have different effects on different ranks - check rank also
1620  if (!IsAuraEffectEqual((*iter)->GetSpellInfo()) && !IsRankOf((*iter)->GetSpellInfo()))
1621  continue;
1622 
1623  // xinef: misc value mismatches
1624  // xinef: commented, checked above
1625  //if (Effects[i].MiscValue != (*iter)->GetMiscValue())
1626  // continue;
1627 
1628  // xinef: should not happen, or effect is not active - stronger one is present
1629  AuraApplication* aurApp = (*iter)->GetBase()->GetApplicationOfTarget(target->GetGUID());
1630  if (!aurApp || !aurApp->IsActive((*iter)->GetEffIndex()))
1631  continue;
1632 
1633  // xinef: assume that all spells are either positive or negative, otherwise they should not be in one group
1634  // xinef: take custom values into account
1635 
1636  int32 basePoints = Effects[i].BasePoints;
1637  int32 duration = GetMaxDuration();
1638 
1639  // xinef: should have the same id, can be different if spell is triggered
1640  // xinef: have to fix spell mods for triggered spell, turn off current spellmodtakingspell for preparing and restore after
1641  if (Player const* player = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
1642  if (player->m_spellModTakingSpell && player->m_spellModTakingSpell->m_spellInfo->Id == Id)
1643  basePoints = player->m_spellModTakingSpell->GetSpellValue()->EffectBasePoints[i];
1644 
1645  int32 curValue = abs(Effects[i].CalcValue(caster, &basePoints));
1646  int32 auraValue = (sFlag & SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_BASE_AMOUNT_CHECK) ?
1647  abs((*iter)->GetSpellInfo()->Effects[(*iter)->GetEffIndex()].CalcValue((*iter)->GetCaster())) :
1648  abs((*iter)->GetAmount());
1649 
1650  // xinef: for same spells, divide amount by stack amount
1651  if (Id == (*iter)->GetId())
1652  auraValue /= (*iter)->GetBase()->GetStackAmount();
1653 
1654  if (curValue < auraValue)
1655  return true;
1656 
1657  // xinef: little hack, if current spell is the same as aura spell, asume it is not stronger
1658  // xinef: if values are the same, duration mods should be taken into account but they are almost always passive
1659  if (curValue == auraValue)
1660  {
1661  if (Id == (*iter)->GetId())
1662  continue;
1663  if (!(*iter)->GetBase()->IsPassive() && duration < (*iter)->GetBase()->GetDuration())
1664  return true;
1665  }
1666  }
1667  }
1668 
1669  return false;
1670 }

1672 bool SpellInfo::IsAuraEffectEqual(SpellInfo const* otherSpellInfo) const
1673 {
1674  uint8 matchCount = 0;
1675  uint8 auraCount = 0;
1676  for (uint8 i = EFFECT_0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1677  {
1678  // xinef: skip non-aura efects
1679  if (!Effects[i].IsAura())
1680  continue;
1681 
1682  bool effectFound = false;
1683  for (uint8 j = EFFECT_0; j < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++j)
1684  {
1685  if (!otherSpellInfo->Effects[j].IsAura())
1686  continue;
1687 
1688  if (Effects[i].ApplyAuraName != otherSpellInfo->Effects[j].ApplyAuraName || Effects[i].MiscValue != otherSpellInfo->Effects[j].MiscValue)
1689  continue;
1690 
1691  effectFound = true;
1692  break;
1693  }
1694 
1695  if (!effectFound)
1696  return false;
1697  ++matchCount;
1698  }
1699 
1700  for (uint8 i = EFFECT_0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1701  {
1702  if (Effects[i].IsAura())
1703  ++auraCount;
1704  if (otherSpellInfo->Effects[i].IsAura())
1705  ++auraCount;
1706  }
1707 
1708  return matchCount * 2 == auraCount;
1709 }

1711 bool SpellInfo::ValidateAttribute6SpellDamageMods(const Unit* caster, const AuraEffect* auraEffect, bool isDot) const
1712 {
1713  // Xinef: no attribute
1714  if (!(AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_IGNORE_CASTER_DAMAGE_MODIFIERS))
1715  return true;
1716 
1717  // Xinef we have a hook to decide which auras should profit to the spell, by default no profits
1718  // Xinef: Scourge Strike - Trigger
1719  if (Id == 70890 && auraEffect)
1720  {
1721  const SpellInfo* auraInfo = auraEffect->GetSpellInfo();
1722  return auraInfo->SpellIconID == 3086 ||
1723  (auraInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_DEATHKNIGHT && (auraInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & flag96(8388608, 64, 16) || auraInfo->SpellIconID == 235 || auraInfo->SpellIconID == 154));
1724  }
1725  // Xinef: Necrosis, no profits for done and taken
1726  else if (Id == 51460)
1727  return false;
1728 
1729  // Xinef: Do not affect dots and auras obtained from items, only affected by self casted auras
1730  return !isDot && auraEffect && (auraEffect->GetAmount() < 0 || (auraEffect->GetCasterGUID() == caster->GetGUID() && auraEffect->GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName == SpellFamilyName)) && !auraEffect->GetBase()->GetCastItemGUID();
1731 }

1733 SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckTarget(Unit const* caster, WorldObject const* target, bool implicit) const
1734 {
1735  if (AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_EXCLUDE_CASTER && caster == target)
1736  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1737 
1738  // check visibility - ignore stealth for implicit (area) targets
1739  if (!(AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_IGNORE_PHASE_SHIFT) && !caster->CanSeeOrDetect(target, implicit))
1740  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1741 
1742  Unit const* unitTarget = target->ToUnit();
1743 
1744  // creature/player specific target checks
1745  if (unitTarget)
1746  {
1747  // xinef: spells cannot be cast if player is in fake combat also
1748  if (AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_ONLY_PEACEFUL_TARGETS && (unitTarget->IsInCombat() || unitTarget->IsPetInCombat()))
1749  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AFFECTING_COMBAT;
1750 
1751  // only spells with SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_ON_GHOSTS can target ghosts
1752  if (((IsRequiringDeadTarget() != 0) != unitTarget->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_GHOST)) && !(IsDeathPersistent() && IsAllowingDeadTarget()))
1753  {
1754  if (AttributesEx3 & SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_ON_GHOSTS)
1755  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NOT_GHOST;
1756  else
1757  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1758  }
1759 
1760  if (caster != unitTarget)
1761  {
1762  if (caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1763  {
1764  // Do not allow these spells to target creatures not tapped by us (Banish, Polymorph, many quest spells)
1765  if (AttributesEx2 & SPELL_ATTR2_CANNOT_CAST_ON_TAPPED)
1766  if (Creature const* targetCreature = unitTarget->ToCreature())
1767  if (targetCreature->hasLootRecipient() && !targetCreature->isTappedBy(caster->ToPlayer()))
1768  return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_CAST_ON_TAPPED;
1769 
1770  if (AttributesCu & SPELL_ATTR0_CU_PICKPOCKET)
1771  {
1772  if (unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1773  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1774  else if ((unitTarget->GetCreatureTypeMask() & CREATURE_TYPEMASK_HUMANOID_OR_UNDEAD) == 0)
1775  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NO_POCKETS;
1776  }
1777 
1778  // Not allow disarm unarmed player
1779  if (Mechanic == MECHANIC_DISARM)
1780  {
1781  if (unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1782  {
1783  Player const* player = unitTarget->ToPlayer();
1784  if (!player->GetWeaponForAttack(BASE_ATTACK, true))
1785  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NO_WEAPONS;
1786  }
1787  else if (!unitTarget->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID))
1788  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NO_WEAPONS;
1789  }
1790  }
1791  }
1792  }
1793  // corpse specific target checks
1794  else if (Corpse const* corpseTarget = target->ToCorpse())
1795  {
1796  // cannot target bare bones
1797  if (corpseTarget->GetType() == CORPSE_BONES)
1798  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1799  // we have to use owner for some checks (aura preventing resurrection for example)
1800  if (Player* owner = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(corpseTarget->GetOwnerGUID()))
1801  unitTarget = owner;
1802  // we're not interested in corpses without owner
1803  else
1804  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1805  }
1806  // other types of objects - always valid
1807  else return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1808 
1809  // corpseOwner and unit specific target checks
1810  if (AttributesEx3 & SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_ON_PLAYER && !unitTarget->ToPlayer())
1811  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NOT_PLAYER;
1812 
1813  if (!IsAllowingDeadTarget() && !unitTarget->IsAlive())
1814  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGETS_DEAD;
1815 
1816  // check this flag only for implicit targets (chain and area), allow to explicitly target units for spells like Shield of Righteousness
1817  if (implicit && AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_DO_NOT_CHAIN_TO_CROWD_CONTROLLED_TARGETS && !unitTarget->CanFreeMove())
1818  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1819 
1820  // checked in Unit::IsValidAttack/AssistTarget, shouldn't be checked for ENTRY targets
1821  //if (!(AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_CAN_TARGET_UNTARGETABLE) && target->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_NOT_SELECTABLE))
1822  // return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1823 
1824  //if (!(AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_NO_AURA_LOG)
1825 
1826  if (!CheckTargetCreatureType(unitTarget))
1827  {
1828  if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1829  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_IS_PLAYER;
1830  else
1831  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1832  }
1833 
1834  // check GM mode and GM invisibility - only for player casts (npc casts are controlled by AI) and negative spells
1835  if (unitTarget != caster && (caster->IsControlledByPlayer() || !IsPositive()) && unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1836  {
1837  if (!unitTarget->ToPlayer()->IsVisible())
1838  return SPELL_FAILED_BM_OR_INVISGOD;
1839 
1840  if (unitTarget->ToPlayer()->IsGameMaster())
1841  return SPELL_FAILED_BM_OR_INVISGOD;
1842  }
1843 
1844  // not allow casting on flying player
1845  if (unitTarget->IsInFlight() && !HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_ALLOW_INFLIGHT_TARGET))
1846  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1847 
1848  /* TARGET_UNIT_MASTER gets blocked here for passengers, because the whole idea of this check is to
1849  not allow passengers to be implicitly hit by spells, however this target type should be an exception,
1850  if this is left it kills spells that award kill credit from vehicle to master (few spells),
1851  the use of these 2 covers passenger target check, logically, if vehicle cast this to master it should always hit
1852  him, because it would be it's passenger, there's no such case where this gets to fail legitimacy, this problem
1853  cannot be solved from within the check in other way since target type cannot be called for the spell currently
1854  Spell examples: [ID - 52864 Devour Water, ID - 52862 Devour Wind, ID - 49370 Wyrmrest Defender: Destabilize Azure Dragonshrine Effect] */
1855  if (!caster->IsVehicle() && caster->GetCharmerOrOwner() != target)
1856  {
1857  if (TargetAuraState && !unitTarget->HasAuraState(AuraStateType(TargetAuraState), this, caster))
1858  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
1859 
1860  if (TargetAuraStateNot && unitTarget->HasAuraState(AuraStateType(TargetAuraStateNot), this, caster))
1861  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
1862  }
1863 
1864  if (TargetAuraSpell && !unitTarget->HasAura(sSpellMgr->GetSpellIdForDifficulty(TargetAuraSpell, caster)))
1865  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
1866 
1867  if (ExcludeTargetAuraSpell && unitTarget->HasAura(sSpellMgr->GetSpellIdForDifficulty(ExcludeTargetAuraSpell, caster)))
1868  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
1869 
1870  if (unitTarget->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_PREVENT_RESURRECTION) && !HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR7_BYPASS_NO_RESURRECTION_AURA))
1871  if (HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_SELF_RESURRECT) || HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_RESURRECT) || HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_RESURRECT_NEW))
1872  return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_CANNOT_BE_RESURRECTED;
1873 
1874  // xinef: check if stronger aura is active
1875  if (IsStrongerAuraActive(caster, unitTarget))
1876  return SPELL_FAILED_AURA_BOUNCED;
1877 
1878  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1879 }

1881 SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckExplicitTarget(Unit const* caster, WorldObject const* target, Item const* itemTarget) const
1882 {
1883  uint32 neededTargets = GetExplicitTargetMask();
1884  if (!target)
1885  {
1886  if (neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK))
1887  if (!(neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM) || !itemTarget)
1888  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1889  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1890  }
1891 
1892  if (Unit const* unitTarget = target->ToUnit())
1893  {
1894  if (neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MINIPET | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PASSENGER))
1895  {
1896  if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY)
1897  if (caster->_IsValidAttackTarget(unitTarget, this))
1898  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1899  if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY
1900  || (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY && caster->IsInPartyWith(unitTarget))
1901  || (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID && caster->IsInRaidWith(unitTarget)))
1902  if (caster->_IsValidAssistTarget(unitTarget, this))
1903  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1904  if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MINIPET)
1905  if (unitTarget->GetGUID() == caster->GetCritterGUID())
1906  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1907  if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PASSENGER)
1908  if (unitTarget->IsOnVehicle(caster))
1909  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1910  return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1911  }
1912  }
1913  return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1914 }

2009 AuraStateType SpellInfo::LoadAuraState() const
2010 {
2011  // Seals
2012  if (GetSpellSpecific() == SPELL_SPECIFIC_SEAL)
2013  return AURA_STATE_JUDGEMENT;
2014 
2015  // Conflagrate aura state on Immolate and Shadowflame
2016  if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK &&
2017  // Immolate
2018  ((SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 4) ||
2019  // Shadowflame
2020  (SpellFamilyFlags[2] & 2)))
2021  return AURA_STATE_CONFLAGRATE;
2022 
2023  // Faerie Fire (druid versions)
2024  if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_DRUID && SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x400)
2025  return AURA_STATE_FAERIE_FIRE;
2026 
2027  // Sting (hunter's pet ability)
2028  if (GetCategory() == 1133)
2029  return AURA_STATE_FAERIE_FIRE;
2030 
2031  // Victorious
2032  if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR && SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x00040000)
2033  return AURA_STATE_WARRIOR_VICTORY_RUSH;
2034 
2035  // Swiftmend state on Regrowth & Rejuvenation
2036  if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_DRUID && SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x50)
2037  return AURA_STATE_SWIFTMEND;
2038 
2039  // Deadly poison aura state
2040  if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE && SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x10000)
2041  return AURA_STATE_DEADLY_POISON;
2042 
2043  // Enrage aura state
2044  if (Dispel == DISPEL_ENRAGE)
2045  return AURA_STATE_ENRAGE;
2046 
2047  // Bleeding aura state
2048  if (GetAllEffectsMechanicMask() & 1 << MECHANIC_BLEED)
2049  return AURA_STATE_BLEEDING;
2050 
2051  if (GetSchoolMask() & SPELL_SCHOOL_MASK_FROST)
2052  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2053  if (Effects[i].IsAura() && (Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN
2054  || Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_ROOT))
2055  return AURA_STATE_FROZEN;
2056 
2057  switch (Id)
2058  {
2059  case 71465: // Divine Surge
2060  case 50241: // Oculus, Drake spell Evasive Maneuvers
2061  return AURA_STATE_UNKNOWN22;
2062  case 9991: // Touch of Zanzil
2063  case 35331: // Black Blood
2064  case 9806: // Phantom Strike
2065  case 35325: // Glowing Blood
2066  case 16498: // Faerie Fire
2067  case 6950:
2068  case 20656:
2069  case 25602:
2070  case 32129:
2071  return AURA_STATE_FAERIE_FIRE;
2072  default:
2073  break;
2074  }
2075 
2076  return AURA_STATE_NONE;
2077 }

2084 SpellSpecificType SpellInfo::LoadSpellSpecific() const
2085 {
2086  switch (SpellFamilyName)
2087  {
2088  case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
2089  {
2090  // Food / Drinks (mostly)
2091  if (AuraInterruptFlags & AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_NOT_SEATED)
2092  {
2093  bool food = false;
2094  bool drink = false;
2095  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2096  {
2097  if (!Effects[i].IsAura())
2098  continue;
2099  switch (Effects[i].ApplyAuraName)
2100  {
2101  // Food
2102  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_REGEN:
2103  case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_HEALTH:
2104  food = true;
2105  break;
2106  // Drink
2107  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_REGEN:
2108  case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_POWER:
2109  drink = true;
2110  break;
2111  default:
2112  break;
2113  }
2114  }
2115 
2116  if (food && drink)
2117  return SPELL_SPECIFIC_FOOD_AND_DRINK;
2118  else if (food)
2119  return SPELL_SPECIFIC_FOOD;
2120  else if (drink)
2121  return SPELL_SPECIFIC_DRINK;
2122  }
2123  // scrolls effects
2124  else
2125  {
2126  SpellInfo const* firstRankSpellInfo = GetFirstRankSpell();
2127  switch (firstRankSpellInfo->Id)
2128  {
2129  case 8118: // Strength
2130  case 8099: // Stamina
2131  case 8112: // Spirit
2132  case 8096: // Intellect
2133  case 8115: // Agility
2134  case 8091: // Armor
2135  return SPELL_SPECIFIC_SCROLL;
2136  }
2137  }
2138  break;
2139  }
2140  case SPELLFAMILY_MAGE:
2141  {
2142  // family flags 18(Molten), 25(Frost/Ice), 28(Mage)
2143  if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x12040000)
2144  return SPELL_SPECIFIC_MAGE_ARMOR;
2145 
2146  // Arcane brillance and Arcane intelect (normal check fails because of flags difference)
2147  if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x400)
2148  return SPELL_SPECIFIC_MAGE_ARCANE_BRILLANCE;
2149 
2150  if ((SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x1000000) && Effects[0].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_CONFUSE)
2151  return SPELL_SPECIFIC_MAGE_POLYMORPH;
2152 
2153  break;
2154  }
2155  case SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK:
2156  {
2157  // only warlock curses have this
2158  if (Dispel == DISPEL_CURSE)

2342 int32 SpellInfo::CalcPowerCost(Unit const* caster, SpellSchoolMask schoolMask, Spell* spell) const
2343 {
2344  // Spell drain all exist power on cast (Only paladin lay of Hands)
2345  if (AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_USE_ALL_MANA)
2346  {
2347  // If power type - health drain all
2348  if (PowerType == POWER_HEALTH)
2349  return caster->GetHealth();
2350  // Else drain all power
2351  if (PowerType < MAX_POWERS)
2352  return caster->GetPower(Powers(PowerType));
2353  LOG_ERROR("spells", "SpellInfo::CalcPowerCost: Unknown power type '%d' in spell %d", PowerType, Id);
2354  return 0;
2355  }
2356 
2357  // Base powerCost
2358  int32 powerCost = ManaCost;
2359  // PCT cost from total amount
2360  if (ManaCostPercentage)
2361  {
2362  switch (PowerType)
2363  {
2364  // health as power used
2365  case POWER_HEALTH:
2366  powerCost += int32(CalculatePct(caster->GetCreateHealth(), ManaCostPercentage));
2367  break;
2368  case POWER_MANA:
2369  powerCost += int32(CalculatePct(caster->GetCreateMana(), ManaCostPercentage));
2370  break;
2371  case POWER_RAGE:
2372  case POWER_FOCUS:
2373  case POWER_ENERGY:
2374  case POWER_HAPPINESS:
2375  powerCost += int32(CalculatePct(caster->GetMaxPower(Powers(PowerType)), ManaCostPercentage));
2376  break;
2377  case POWER_RUNE:
2378  case POWER_RUNIC_POWER:
2379  LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "CalculateManaCost: Not implemented yet!");
2380  break;
2381  default:
2382  LOG_ERROR("spells", "CalculateManaCost: Unknown power type '%d' in spell %d", PowerType, Id);
2383  return 0;
2384  }
2385  }
2386  SpellSchools school = GetFirstSchoolInMask(schoolMask);
2387  // Flat mod from caster auras by spell school
2388  powerCost += caster->GetInt32Value(static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_POWER_COST_MODIFIER) + school);
2389 
2390  // Shiv - costs 20 + weaponSpeed*10 energy (apply only to non-triggered spell with energy cost)
2391  if (AttributesEx4 & SPELL_ATTR4_WEAPON_SPEED_COST_SCALING)
2392  {
2393  uint32 speed = 0;
2394  if (SpellShapeshiftEntry const* ss = sSpellShapeshiftStore.LookupEntry(caster->GetShapeshiftForm()))
2395  speed = ss->attackSpeed;
2396  else
2397  {
2398  WeaponAttackType slot = BASE_ATTACK;
2399  if (AttributesEx3 & SPELL_ATTR3_REQUIRES_OFF_HAND_WEAPON)
2400  slot = OFF_ATTACK;
2401 
2402  speed = caster->GetAttackTime(slot);
2403  }
2404 
2405  powerCost += speed / 100;
2406  }
2407 
2408  // Apply cost mod by spell
2409  if (Player* modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
2410  modOwner->ApplySpellMod(Id, SPELLMOD_COST, powerCost, spell);
2411 
2412  if (!caster->IsControlledByPlayer())
2413  {
2414  if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_SCALES_WITH_CREATURE_LEVEL))
2415  {
2416  GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* spellScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.LookupEntry(SpellLevel - 1);
2417  GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* casterScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.LookupEntry(caster->getLevel() - 1);
2418  if (spellScaler && casterScaler)
2419  powerCost *= casterScaler->ratio / spellScaler->ratio;
2420  }
2421  }
2422 
2423  // PCT mod from user auras by school
2424  powerCost = int32(powerCost * (1.0f + caster->GetFloatValue(static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_POWER_COST_MULTIPLIER) + school)));
2425  if (powerCost < 0)
2426  powerCost = 0;
2427  return powerCost;
2428 }

2533 void SpellInfo::_InitializeExplicitTargetMask()
2534 {
2535  bool srcSet = false;
2536  bool dstSet = false;
2537  uint32 targetMask = Targets;
2538  // prepare target mask using effect target entries
2539  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2540  {
2541  if (!Effects[i].IsEffect())
2542  continue;
2543  targetMask |= Effects[i].TargetA.GetExplicitTargetMask(srcSet, dstSet);
2544  targetMask |= Effects[i].TargetB.GetExplicitTargetMask(srcSet, dstSet);
2545 
2546  // add explicit target flags based on spell effects which have EFFECT_IMPLICIT_TARGET_EXPLICIT and no valid target provided
2547  if (Effects[i].GetImplicitTargetType() != EFFECT_IMPLICIT_TARGET_EXPLICIT)
2548  continue;
2549 
2550  // extend explicit target mask only if valid targets for effect could not be provided by target types
2551  uint32 effectTargetMask = Effects[i].GetMissingTargetMask(srcSet, dstSet, targetMask);
2552 
2553  // don't add explicit object/dest flags when spell has no max range
2554  if (GetMaxRange(true) == 0.0f && GetMaxRange(false) == 0.0f)
2555  effectTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION);
2556  targetMask |= effectTargetMask;
2557  }
2558  ExplicitTargetMask = targetMask;
2559 }

2561 bool SpellInfo::_IsPositiveEffect(uint8 effIndex, bool deep) const
2562 {
2563  // not found a single positive spell with this attribute
2564  if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_AURA_IS_DEBUFF))
2565  return false;
2566 
2567  switch (Mechanic)
2568  {
2569  case MECHANIC_IMMUNE_SHIELD:
2570  return true;
2571  default:
2572  break;
2573  }
2574 
2575  // Special case: effects which determine positivity of whole spell
2576  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2577  {
2578  if (Effects[i].IsAura() && Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_STEALTH)
2579  return true;
2580  }
2581 
2582  switch (Effects[effIndex].Effect)
2583  {
2584  case SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY:
2585  // some explicitly required dummy effect sets
2586  switch (Id)
2587  {
2588  case 28441:
2589  return false; // AB Effect 000
2590  default:
2591  break;
2592  }
2593  break;
2594  // always positive effects (check before target checks that provided non-positive result in some case for positive effects)
2595  case SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL:
2596  case SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL:
2597  case SPELL_EFFECT_SKILL_STEP:
2598  case SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL_PCT:
2599  case SPELL_EFFECT_ENERGIZE_PCT:
2600  return true;
2601  case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_ENEMY:
2602  return false;
2603 
2604  case SPELL_EFFECT_GAMEOBJECT_DAMAGE:
2605  return false;
2606 
2607  case SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE:
2608  {
2609  bool only = true;
2610  for (int i = EFFECT_0; i <= EFFECT_2; ++i)
2611  {

2613  only = false;
2614  if (Effects[effIndex].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_GAMEOBJECT_DAMAGE)
2615  return false;
2616  }
2617  // effects with school damage only cannot be positive...
2618  if (only)
2619  return false;
2620  break;
2621  }
2622  case SPELL_EFFECT_KNOCK_BACK:
2623  case SPELL_EFFECT_KNOCK_BACK_DEST:
2624  {
2625  for (int i = EFFECT_0; i <= EFFECT_2; ++i)
2626  if (Effects[effIndex].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_GAMEOBJECT_DAMAGE)
2627  return false;
2628  break;
2629  }
2630 
2631  // non-positive aura use
2632  case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA:
2633  case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_FRIEND:
2634  {
2635  switch (Effects[effIndex].ApplyAuraName)
2636  {
2637  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_DONE: // dependent from bas point sign (negative -> negative)
2638  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STAT:
2639  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SKILL:
2640  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DODGE_PERCENT:
2641  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_PCT:
2642  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_DONE:
2643  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_DONE:

2645  return false;
2646  break;
2647  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_TAKEN: // dependent from bas point sign (positive -> negative)
2648  if (Effects[effIndex].CalcValue() > 0)
2649  return false;
2650  break;
2651  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CRIT_PCT:
2652  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SPELL_CRIT_CHANCE:
2653  if (Effects[effIndex].CalcValue() > 0)
2654  return true; // some expected positive spells have SPELL_ATTR1_NEGATIVE
2655  break;
2656  case SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER:
2657  return true;
2658  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
2659  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
2660  if (!deep)
2661  {

2682  break;
2683  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_PACIFY_SILENCE:
2684  if (Id == 24740) // Wisp Costume
2685  return true;
2686  return false;
2687  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_ROOT:
2688  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SILENCE:
2689  case SPELL_AURA_GHOST:
2690  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:

2700  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DECREASE_SPEED: // used in positive spells also

2704  // but not this if this first effect (didn't find better check)

2708  case SPELL_AURA_MECHANIC_IMMUNITY:

2724  case SPELL_AURA_ADD_PCT_MODIFIER:

2745  return false;

2747  }
2748  break;
2749  default:
2750  break;
2751  }
2752  break;
2753  }
2754  default:
2755  break;
2756  }
2757  break;
2758  }
2759  default:
2760  break;
2761  }
2762 
2763  // non-positive targets

2767  // negative spell if triggered spell is negative
2768  if (!deep && !Effects[effIndex].ApplyAuraName && Effects[effIndex].TriggerSpell)
2769  {
2770  if (SpellInfo const* spellTriggeredProto = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(Effects[effIndex].TriggerSpell))
2771  if (!spellTriggeredProto->_IsPositiveSpell())
2772  return false;
2773  }
2774 
2775  // ok, positive
2776  return true;
2777 }

2779 bool SpellInfo::_IsPositiveSpell() const
2780 {
2781  // spells with at least one negative effect are considered negative
2782  // some self-applied spells have negative effects but in self casting case negative check ignored.
2783  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2784  if (!_IsPositiveEffect(i, true))
2785  return false;
2786  return true;
2787 }

2789 bool SpellInfo::_IsPositiveTarget(uint32 targetA, uint32 targetB)
2790 {
2791  // non-positive targets
2792  switch (targetA)
2793  {
2794  case TARGET_UNIT_NEARBY_ENEMY:
2795  case TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_ENEMY:
2796  case TARGET_UNIT_SRC_AREA_ENEMY:
2797  case TARGET_UNIT_DEST_AREA_ENEMY:
2798  case TARGET_UNIT_CONE_ENEMY_24:
2799  case TARGET_UNIT_CONE_ENEMY_54:
2800  case TARGET_UNIT_CONE_ENEMY_104:

2802  case TARGET_DEST_TARGET_ENEMY:
2803  return false;
2804  default:
2805  break;
2806  }
2807  if (targetB)

2809  return true;

2812 void SpellInfo::_UnloadImplicitTargetConditionLists()
2813 {
2814  // find the same instances of ConditionList and delete them.
2815  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2816  {
2817  ConditionList* cur = Effects[i].ImplicitTargetConditions;
2818  if (!cur)
2819  continue;
2820  for (uint8 j = i; j < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++j)
2821  {
2822  if (Effects[j].ImplicitTargetConditions == cur)
2823  Effects[j].ImplicitTargetConditions = nullptr;
2824  }
2825  delete cur;
2826  }
